FBIS3-54963 "drsov003_b_94050" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Baykonur To Launch Soyuz Rocket Complex 8 Jan LD0401221494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 4 Jan 94 LD0401221494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] According to a report by the press center of the Russian military space forces, on 8 January a Soyuz TM-18 rocket complex will be launched from the Baykonur cosmodrome. The crew consists of the commander, Colonel Viktor Afanasyev, the on-board engineer, Yuriy Usachev, and Doctor (Valeriy Polyakov). The program of the flight has been arranged in such a way that Viktor Afanasyev and Yuriy Usachev will spend 179 days in orbit, and Doctor (Valeriy Polyakov) is to spend 429 days in orbit -- no one has spent that long of time in space before.
